transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Yeah, thanks for calling Viagra. How can I help you?

Speaker 2: Yeah, I received an order from Scorablue a few days ago, or Phil Denafow, Phil? Okay, from the Scorablue company.

Speaker 1: The prescription bottle does not have anything about the... all it says is basically just Viagra, not the Viagra that's on your ads and things. What's going on with that?

Speaker 2: Oh, okay, so you're under the impression you might have gotten the wrong thing there. You said this is Mr. Grog?

Speaker 1: Yes.

Speaker 2: What's your... do you have those pills there with you?

Speaker 1: Yes, I do.

Speaker 2: What do the markings say on the actual physical pill? Let me know, please, Mr. Grog.

Speaker 1: Let me see if I can get this lid off of you.

Speaker 2: Take your time. Yeah, if you did get the incorrect thing, I will definitely send you a replacement order stat, of course.

Speaker 1: Okay, it says AC339.

Speaker 2: Yeah, so those are incorrect, Mr. Grog. Those are very similar to what those guys get from the VA. They're still generic Viagra, but it's definitely not our AGV.

Speaker 1: What I'm going to do for you, I have you at 1607 Osceola Street, Johnson City. I'm going to, of course, send you a replacement order at no cost.

Speaker 2: I'm going to expedite this. You'll see it come out in the next few days, probably by Tuesday at the latest. I'm really sorry about that mix-up there.

Speaker 1: That's no problem. You might want to alert the people at Go-Go Meds that they've got a problem.

Speaker 2: Oh, yeah, no, they're working on it. We have gotten a few other calls like this.

Speaker 1: Okay, so this came out of the pharmacy in Southgate, Kentucky?

Speaker 2: Yeah, that's where we ship out of, Kentucky.

Speaker 1: But, yeah, I'm going to alert them now, and you'll see this order come out really soon next week, okay?

Speaker 2: All right, I appreciate your help. Thank you.

Speaker 1: Thank you, Sam. Bye-bye now.
